+# Budgetary Cloud Estimator (Pilot MVP)
+
+A Flask app that provides deterministic AWS/Azure budgetary estimates from manual VM inputs or an RVTools Excel upload.
+
+## Quick start
+
+```bash
+python -m venv .venv
+source .venv/bin/activate  # Windows: .venv\Scripts\activate
+python -m pip install --upgrade pip
+python -m pip install -r requirements.txt
+python run_local.py
+```
+
+Open: <http://localhost:5000>
+
+## If install fails (proxy/network)
+
+If you see errors like `403 Forbidden` during `pip install`, configure your package index/proxy first, for example:
+
+```bash
+python -m pip install -r requirements.txt \
+  --index-url https://pypi.org/simple
+```
+
+Or use your internal mirror:
+
+```bash
+python -m pip install -r requirements.txt \
+  --index-url <your-company-pypi-url>
+```
+
+## Useful endpoints
+
+- `/` main estimate form
+- `/pdf` download generated PDF draft
+- `/health` lightweight health check
+
+## Notes
+
+- The large logo is rendered as a page background watermark across web pages.
+- PDF output includes a watermark on every page.
+- Create `data/KILL_SWITCH` to temporarily disable estimation.
